Shi, Bian &amp; Chang
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[868,962,1320,1344]" pageId="1" pageNumber="164">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="164" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1388,1593]" pageId="1" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1388,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="164">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new genus resembles the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fischer, 1853" authorityName="Fischer" authorityYear="1853" box="[793,1075,1389,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Cyrtaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[793,900,1390,1413]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="164">Cyrtaspis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fischer" box="[914,1075,1389,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="164" refString="Fischer, L. H. (1853) Orthoptera Europaea. Accedunt tabulae lapidibus incisae XVIII, quarum ultima coloribus partim illustrata. Lipsiae (= Leipzig), G. Engelmann, 454 pp., pls 1 - 18." type="book chapter" year="1853">
Fischer, 
<number box="[1016,1075,1389,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="164" value="1853.0">1853</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter in following characters: male pronotum with disc flat, metazona not raised, posterior margin of lateral lobe slightly broadened; tenth abdominal tergite distinctly specialized, longer and enlarged, posterior area bifurcate; cercus short and stout; genitalia longer than subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
